This directory ('tools') contains scripts found around the internet by
different authors, or written for the Waverous project.

chroot.sh: This shows the basics on how to create a chroot environment
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chroot) to run your server, for security
reasons

moo2xml.py: convert your MOO database file to XML

moobrowser.c: given different command line arguments, this tool will
display data from your MOO database

test.exp: an experimental script to use Expect
(http://www.nist.gov/el/msid/expect.cfm) to test a running server

